// STRESS 5: edge-case literals + chained set + empty parens + numbers
// edges: float literal, negative int, call with multiple args, set with quoted string
Create a console application.

Make a function called area(double r) that returns a double:
    return 3.14159

When the program starts:
    set pi = 3.14
    set neg = -7
    set msg = "hello \"world\"\n\\done"
    set empty = ""
    call printf("x=%d y=%s", 42, "ok")
    print pi
    print neg
    print msg
    print empty
